              "id": "glog-1b3af599-9c21-402a-948a-ee3ed8c33312",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "### Description\n\nThe vulnerability arises when parsing untrusted XML data using `xml.dom.minidom.parse`, which can be exploited through XML External Entity (XXE) attacks. These attacks can lead to exposure of sensitive data, denial of service, or other security issues. The `xml.dom.minidom` module does not provide protection against these attacks by default. To mitigate this risk, it is recommended to use the `defusedxml` library, which provides a safer alternative for parsing XML data.\n\n### General Mitigation Advice\n\n- Avoid parsing XML data from untrusted sources using `xml.dom.minidom`.\n- Use the `defusedxml` library, which is specifically designed to prevent XML-related vulnerabilities.\n- If you must use the standard library, ensure that `defusedxml.defuse_stdlib()` is invoked to patch the standard library modules.\n\n### Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\nReplace the vulnerable code:\n\n```python\nmanifest = DOM.parse(manifestFullPath)\n```\n\nWith the safer alternative using `defusedxml`:\n\n```python\nfrom defusedxml.minidom import parse\n\nmanifest = parse(manifestFullPath)\n```\n\n### Library Dependencies\n\nTo execute the code example properly, the following library is required:\n\n- `defusedxml`\n\nYou can install it using pip:\n\n```bash\npip install defusedxml\n```\n\n### Relevant OWASP Resources\n\n- [OWASP XML External Entity (XXE) Prevention Cheat Sheet](https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/XML_External_Entity_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html)\n\n### Common Weakness Enumeration (CWE)\n\n- [CWE-611: Improper Restriction of XML External Entity Reference ('XXE')](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/611.html)"
